DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;


$h0 = random(40,80,10);
$x0 = 10;
$dx = 20;
$x1 = 30;
$h1 = random(10,25,5);
$quot = $h1/$h0;
$b = ($quot)**(1/$dx);
$b_rd = round(10000*$b)/10000;
$a = $h0*$b**(-10);
$a_rd = round($a*10000)/10000;
$ans = "($a_rd)*($b_rd)^x";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 33:
$BR $SPACE $BR
Find a formula for the EXPONENTIAL function which satisfies the given conditions:
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
\( g($x0) = $h0 \) $SPACE $SPACE and $SPACE $SPACE \( g($x1) = $h1 \)
$BR
\( g(x) = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
(be sure to approximate your values for $BITALIC a $EITALIC and $BITALIC b $EITALIC in your formula to at least 4 decimal places to avoid significant rounding error)

END_TEXT

ANS( fun_cmp($ans,vars=>'x'));


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 

Since \( g(x)=ab^x \), \( g($x0)= ab^{$x0} \) and \( g($x1)=ab^{$x1} \).
$BR
Since we know that \( g($x0)=$h0 \) and \( g($x1)=$h1 \), we can say that \( ab^{$x0} = $h0 \) and \( ab^{$x1} = $h1 \).  Forming ratios, we have
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( \frac{ab^{$x0}}{ab^{$x1}} = \frac{$h1}{$h0} \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( b^{($x1 - $x0)} = b^{$dx} = \frac{$h1}{$h0} \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( b = \left( \frac{$h1}{$h0} \right)^{1/$dx} \approx $b_rd \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
Thus, our formula is \( g(x)=a($b_rd)^x \).  Use \( g($x0)=a($b_rd)^{$x0} \) and \( g($x0)=$h0 \) to get
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( a($b_rd)^{$x0} = $h0 \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( a = \frac{$h0}{$b_rd^{$x0}} \approx $a_rd \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
Therefore \( g(x) = ($a_rd)($b_rd)^x \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.